---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Elements">
  <h1>Elements</h1>
  <p>
    <code>@hexpunk/core/elements.css</code> ships a token-driven baseline for native HTML
    primitives — paragraphs, links, lists, tables, code, form fields. Import it once at the
    document root and raw HTML in your app picks up the design system's typography, colour,
    focus ring, and forced-colors fallbacks. No <code>&lt;hp-*&gt;</code> wrapper required.
  </p>

  <hp-banner tone="neutral">
    Two layers in one file. The <strong>bare reset</strong> auto-applies to every native
    element. The <strong>.hp-prose</strong> class is an opt-in rhythm scope for long-form
    content — see the <a href="/getting-started/prose">Prose</a> page.
  </hp-banner>

  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <hp-code language="jsx">{`import "@hexpunk/core/tokens.dark.css";
import "@hexpunk/core/tokens.light.css";
import "@hexpunk/core/elements.css";

export default () => (
  <p>Hello, hex world.</p>
);`}</hp-code>

  <h2>Headings</h2>
  <hp-demo caption="h1 through h6">
    <div>
      <h1>Heading 1 — display lg</h1>
      <h2>Heading 2 — headline lg</h2>
      <h3>Heading 3 — headline md</h3>
      <h4>Heading 4 — title md</h4>
      <h5>Heading 5 — label md (uppercase)</h5>
      <h6>Heading 6 — label sm (uppercase)</h6>
    </div>
    <hp-code slot="code" language="jsx">{`import "@hexpunk/core/elements.css";

export default () => (
  <>
    <h1>Heading 1 — display lg</h1>
    <h2>Heading 2 — headline lg</h2>
    <h3>Heading 3 — headline md</h3>
    <h4>Heading 4 — title md</h4>
    <h5>Heading 5 — label md (uppercase)</h5>
    <h6>Heading 6 — label sm (uppercase)</h6>
  </>
);`}</hp-code>
  </hp-demo>
  <p>
    Headings carry zero default margin so they compose freely. Use <code>.hp-prose</code>
    on a wrapping element to opt into vertical rhythm.
  </p>

  <h2>Inline text</h2>
  <hp-demo caption="Emphasis, marks, abbreviations">
    <div>
      <p>
        Paragraphs default to <code>--hp-on-surface</code>. <strong>Strong</strong> and
        <b>b</b> tighten weight; <em>emphasis</em> and <i>i</i> italicise.
        <small>Small text drops to body-sm.</small>
      </p>
      <p>
        <mark>Marked text</mark> uses the warn container tokens.
        <del>Deleted</del> strikes through; <ins>inserted</ins> underlines with the
        secondary hue. Press <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>K</kbd> for command palettes —
        <abbr title="Keyboard">kbd</abbr> reads as a key cap.
      </p>
      <p>
        H<sub>2</sub>O and E = mc<sup>2</sup>. Variables read as <var>x</var>, samples as
        <samp>OK</samp>.
      </p>
    </div>
    <hp-code slot="code" language="jsx">{`import "@hexpunk/core/elements.css";

export default () => (
  <>
    <p>
      <strong>Strong</strong> / <b>b</b>, <em>emphasis</em> / <i>i</i>,
      <small>small text</small>, <mark>marked</mark>, <del>del</del>,
      <ins>ins</ins>, <kbd>Ctrl</kbd>, <abbr title="Keyboard">kbd</abbr>.
    </p>
    <p>H<sub>2</sub>O — E = mc<sup>2</sup>. <var>x</var> / <samp>OK</samp>.</p>
  </>
);`}</hp-code>
  </hp-demo>

  <h2>Links</h2>
  <hp-demo caption="Anchor as text">
    <p>
      Raw <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> is the *anchor-as-text* primitive — for in-sentence
      references like a <a href="#">link to elsewhere</a>. For *anchor-as-affordance*
      (hover trace, hex geometry), reach for
      <a href="/components/navigation/hp-link"><code>&lt;hp-link&gt;</code></a> or
      <a href="/components/primitives/hp-cell"><code>&lt;hp-cell variant="anchor"&gt;</code></a>.
    </p>
    <hp-code slot="code" language="jsx">{`import "@hexpunk/core/elements.css";

export default () => (
  <p>
    Visit <a href="https://example.com">example.com</a> for details.
  </p>
);`}</hp-code>
  </hp-demo>

  <h2>Code</h2>
  <hp-demo caption="Inline and block">
    <div>
      <p>
        Inline <code>const x = 1</code> renders as a chip. Block-level code uses
        <code>&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;</code>:
      </p>
      <pre><code>function hex(q, r) &#123;
  return [q * (3 / 2), r * Math.sqrt(3) + q * Math.sqrt(3) / 2];
&#125;</code></pre>
    </div>
    <hp-code slot="code" language="jsx">{`import "@hexpunk/core/elements.css";

export default () => (
  <>
    <p>Inline <code>const x = 1</code> reads as a chip.</p>
    <pre><code>{\`function hex(q, r) {
  return [q * (3 / 2), r * Math.sqrt(3) + q * Math.sqrt(3) / 2];
}\`}</code></pre>
  </>
);`}</hp-code>
  </hp-demo>
  <p>
    For syntax-highlighted code with line numbers and per-line hover, use
    <a href="/components/primitives/hp-code"><code>&lt;hp-code&gt;</code></a> instead — it
    accepts a consumer-registered highlighter.
  </p>

  <h2>Blockquote</h2>
  <hp-demo caption="Citation with attribution">
    <blockquote>
      <p>The system is the source of truth — the chrome is just the surface.</p>
      <cite>— Hexpunk DESIGN.md</cite>
    </blockquote>
    <hp-code slot="code" language="jsx">{`import "@hexpunk/core/elements.css";

export default () => (
  <blockquote>
    <p>The system is the source of truth — the chrome is just the surface.</p>
    <cite>— Hexpunk DESIGN.md</cite>
  </blockquote>
);`}</hp-code>
  </hp-demo>

  <h2>Lists</h2>
  <hp-demo caption="Unordered, ordered, and definition lists">
    <div class="hp-prose">
      <ul>
        <li>Atoms — single-hex elements (<code>hp-cell</code>, <code>hp-icon</code>)</li>
        <li>Molecules — composed structures (<code>hp-grid</code>, <code>hp-cluster</code>)</li>
        <li>
          Primitives — the bigger ideas
          <ul>
            <li>Bonding (adjacency)</li>
            <li>Linking (arcs at distance)</li>
            <li>Unfolding (in-place / overlay / camera-zoom)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <ol>
        <li>Read DESIGN.md</li>
        <li>Read PLAN.md</li>
        <li>Pick a step, propose, confirm, ship</li>
      </ol>
      <dl>
        <dt>Cell</dt>
        <dd>Universal labelled hex element with interactive variants.</dd>
        <dt>Cluster</dt>
        <dd>Canonical 5-hex rosette layout.</dd>
        <dt>Tether</dt>
        <dd>Curved arc between two anchors.</dd>
      </dl>
    </div>
    <hp-code slot="code" language="jsx">{`import "@hexpunk/core/elements.css";

export default () => (
  <div class="hp-prose">
    <ul>
      <li>Atoms — single-hex elements</li>
      <li>
        Molecules — composed structures
        <ul>
          <li>Bonding (adjacency)</li>
          <li>Linking (arcs at distance)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <ol>
      <li>Read DESIGN.md</li>
      <li>Pick a step, propose, confirm, ship</li>
    </ol>
    <dl>
      <dt>Cell</dt>
      <dd>Universal labelled hex element.</dd>
    </dl>
  </div>
);`}</hp-code>
  </hp-demo>
  <p>
    Bullet glyphs use the secondary hue via <code>::marker</code>. Padding shown here comes
    from the <code>.hp-prose</code> wrapper — bare-reset lists ship with zero padding so
    consumers control list indentation per-surface.
  </p>

  <h2>Tables</h2>
  <hp-demo caption="Caption, header, cells">
    <table>
      <caption>Density modes</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Mode</th>
          <th>Cell sm</th>
          <th>Cell md</th>
          <th>Cell lg</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>compact</td><td>44</td><td>80</td><td>140</td></tr>
        <tr><td>default</td><td>50</td><td>100</td><td>180</td></tr>
        <tr><td>comfortable</td><td>60</td><td>120</td><td>220</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <hp-code slot="code" language="jsx">{`import "@hexpunk/core/elements.css";

export default () => (
  <table>
    <caption>Density modes</caption>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Mode</th>
        <th>Cell sm</th>
        <th>Cell md</th>
        <th>Cell lg</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>compact</td><td>44</td><td>80</td><td>140</td></tr>
      <tr><td>default</td><td>50</td><td>100</td><td>180</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
);`}</hp-code>
  </hp-demo>

  <h2>Details / summary</h2>
  <hp-demo caption="Native disclosure">
    <div>
      <details>
        <summary>What's a soulslike boss?</summary>
        <p>
          Stamina-gated melee fight with parry windows and phase escalation — see
          <code>PLAN.soulslike-adr.md</code> in the snecko repo.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details open>
        <summary>Open by default</summary>
        <p>The <code>open</code> attribute starts the disclosure expanded.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
    <hp-code slot="code" language="jsx">{`import "@hexpunk/core/elements.css";

export default () => (
  <>
    <details>
      <summary>What's a soulslike boss?</summary>
      <p>Stamina-gated melee fight with parry windows.</p>
    </details>
    <details open>
      <summary>Open by default</summary>
      <p>The <code>open</code> attribute starts expanded.</p>
    </details>
  </>
);`}</hp-code>
  </hp-demo>

  <h2>Horizontal rule</h2>
  <hp-demo caption="Section divider">
    <div>
      <p>Above the rule.</p>
      <hr>
      <p>Below the rule.</p>
    </div>
    <hp-code slot="code" language="jsx">{`import "@hexpunk/core/elements.css";

export default () => (
  <>
    <p>Above the rule.</p>
    <hr />
    <p>Below the rule.</p>
  </>
);`}</hp-code>
  </hp-demo>

  <h2>Form primitives</h2>
  <p>
    Raw form inputs get tokenised typography, restrained borders, and a focus ring that
    matches <code>hp-base</code>. They deliberately don't carry hex geometry — reach for
    <a href="/components/forms/hp-button"><code>&lt;hp-button&gt;</code></a>,
    <a href="/components/forms/hp-select"><code>&lt;hp-select&gt;</code></a>, etc. when
    you want the full system aesthetic.
  </p>

  <hp-demo caption="Text inputs">
    <form
      onsubmit="event.preventDefault()"
      style="display: grid; gap: 12px; max-width: 32rem;"
    >
      <label>
        Name
        <input type="text" placeholder="Hissalia" style="display: block; width: 100%;">
      </label>
      <label>
        Email (validates on blur)
        <input type="email" required placeholder="izzy@example.com" style="display: block; width: 100%;">
      </label>
      <label>
        Bio
        <textarea placeholder="Tell us about your hex obsession" style="display: block; width: 100%;"></textarea>
      </label>
      <label>
        Country
        <select style="display: block; width: 100%;">
          <option>United Kingdom</option>
          <option>United States</option>
          <option>Japan</option>
        </select>
      </label>
    </form>
    <hp-code slot="code" language="jsx">{`import "@hexpunk/core/elements.css";

export default () => (
  <form>
    <label>
      Name
      <input type="text" placeholder="Hissalia" />
    </label>
    <label>
      Email
      <input type="email" required placeholder="izzy@example.com" />
    </label>
    <label>
      Bio
      <textarea />
    </label>
    <label>
      Country
      <select>
        <option>United Kingdom</option>
        <option>United States</option>
      </select>
    </label>
  </form>
);`}</hp-code>
  </hp-demo>

  <hp-demo caption="Buttons, checkbox, radio, range">
    <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 16px; align-items: center;">
      <button>raw button</button>
      <button disabled>disabled</button>
      <label><input type="checkbox" checked> Subscribe</label>
      <label><input type="radio" name="r" checked> A</label>
      <label><input type="radio" name="r"> B</label>
      <input type="range" min="0" max="100" value="42">
      <input type="color" value="#00cc88">
    </div>
    <hp-code slot="code" language="jsx">{`import "@hexpunk/core/elements.css";

export default () => (
  <>
    <button>raw button</button>
    <button disabled>disabled</button>
    <label><input type="checkbox" checked /> Subscribe</label>
    <label><input type="radio" name="r" /> A</label>
    <input type="range" min="0" max="100" value="42" />
    <input type="color" value="#00cc88" />
  </>
);`}</hp-code>
  </hp-demo>

  <hp-demo caption="Fieldset + legend">
    <fieldset style="max-width: 32rem;">
      <legend>Display preferences</legend>
      <label style="display: block;"><input type="checkbox"> Reduce motion</label>
      <label style="display: block;"><input type="checkbox" checked> Show focus rings</label>
      <label style="display: block;"><input type="checkbox"> High contrast</label>
    </fieldset>
    <hp-code slot="code" language="jsx">{`import "@hexpunk/core/elements.css";

export default () => (
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Display preferences</legend>
    <label><input type="checkbox" /> Reduce motion</label>
    <label><input type="checkbox" checked /> Show focus rings</label>
    <label><input type="checkbox" /> High contrast</label>
  </fieldset>
);`}</hp-code>
  </hp-demo>

  <h2>What this file does NOT do</h2>
  <ul class="hp-prose">
    <li>Restyle <code>&lt;hp-*&gt;</code> elements — they live in shadow DOM and own their own chrome.</li>
    <li>Repaint <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> / <code>&lt;input&gt;</code> as full hp-button / hp-input lookalikes — hex geometry stays reserved for the components.</li>
    <li>Force a max-width or font-size root override — the page shell is yours.</li>
  </ul>
</Layout>
